## Third-party data sources

This software ingests and visualises F1 race data from third-party sources
that are independently licensed. The MIT licence above covers the source code
in this repository and does NOT extend to the underlying data:

- **FastF1 telemetry & timing** — accessed via the open-source FastF1 library
  (MIT-licensed). Underlying timing data is the property of Formula One World
  Championship Limited and used here under fair-use for non-commercial
  predictive modelling.
- **Jolpica / Ergast-compatible historical archive** — accessed via the
  Jolpica public API. Underlying data is sourced from publicly-published
  race classifications.
- **Wikimedia Commons circuit photography** — individual photos are released
  under various Creative Commons licences (CC BY-SA 3.0, CC BY 4.0, CC0).
  Attribution is in
  [`website/src/lib/raceArt.ts`](website/src/lib/raceArt.ts) where each URL
  is anchored to the source page.
- **Driver headshots** under [`website/public/headshots/`](website/public/headshots/)
  are derived from publicly-published team and Formula One promotional
  imagery and are used under fair-use for non-commercial analytical
  visualisation. No claim of original authorship is made.

The curated race-art manifest in [`website/src/lib/raceArt.ts`](website/src/lib/raceArt.ts)
— the URLs themselves, not the underlying photos — is released under CC0.

If you are a rights-holder for any image referenced here and would like it
removed or re-attributed, please open an issue in this repository.
